article.headline: Atkinson's complete game nets Tar Heels a victory
article.linkText: Reserve powers No. 12 North Carolina past DePaul
article.story:
HONOLULU (AP) -- Reserve La'Tangela Atkinson had 12 points, and
led North Carolina (No. 12 ESPN/USA Today; No. 11 Associated Press) with 10 rebounds and four assists as the
Tar Heels shut down DePaul 82-66 Friday in the first round of the
Rainbow Wahine Classic.

	   Coretta Brown made four 3-point baskets and scored 14 points for
the Tar Heels (3-0), who made the defensive adjustments needed to
hold off DePaul.

	   The North Carolina defense forced the Blue Demons (1-1) to take
28 shots from 3-point range, making only seven. The Tar Heels held
DePaul, which got 16 points nine rebounds from Jamie Smith, to
just six points in the final seven minutes.

	   Charlene Smith added 15 points for DePaul.

	   Jenni Dent and Ashley Luke had 11 points apiece for North
Carolina.
